---
import Layout from "../layouts/layouts.astro";
import PhotoPlaceholder from "../components/PhotoPlaceholder.astro";
---

<Layout title="Quick Start" currentPath={Astro.url.pathname}>
	<section class="hero">
		<h1>Quick Start</h1>
		<p class="subhead">
			This page lists the essentials for arriving, getting set up, and settling in during your first 10 minutes.
		</p>

		<section class="section">
			<div class="checklistCard">
				<h2>First 10 minutes</h2>
				<ol class="checklist">
					<li><a href="#parking">Park (don’t block the laneway)</a></li>
					<li><a href="#keys">Get keys from the lockbox</a></li>
					<li><a href="#electricity">Turn on electricity (fuse box)</a></li>
					<li><a href="#mains">Turn on water &amp; gas mains</a></li>
					<li><a href="#hot-water">Check hot water (boiler button)</a></li>
					<li><a href="#hob">Check the gas hob is working</a></li>
				</ol>
			</div>
		</section>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Address</h2>
		<div class="callout">
			<strong>Nardelli Nespolo</strong><br />
			Località Nardelli, 31, 06061 Nardelli PG, Italy
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section" id="parking">
		<div class="stepCard">
			<div class="stepText">
				<h2>Parking</h2>
				<p>
					Please park close to the front door. <strong>Do not block the laneway at the side of the house</strong>
					— this access route is needed for neighbours and farming access.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="stepMedia">
				<img
					class="instructionPhoto"
					src="/photos/Parking.jpeg"
					alt="Parking near the front door (do not block the laneway)"
					loading="lazy"
				/>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section" id="keys">
		<div class="stepCard">
			<div class="stepText">
				<h2>Keys (lockbox)</h2>
				<p>
					There is a lockbox attached to the frame of the garden gate. It contains the key to the{" "}
					<strong>front door</strong> and the <strong>garden gate</strong>. You already have the code.
				</p>

				<ul>
					<li>
						<strong>Front door key tip:</strong> to remove the key from the front door, you may need to turn it{" "}
						<strong>half a turn back</strong> first.
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Please leave the garden key in the lockbox</strong> (and scramble the lockbox code) unless
						you are using it — the gardener may need access.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="stepMedia">
	<div class="stepMedia">
	<div class="mediaRow">
		<img
			class="instructionPhoto"
			src="/photos/Lockbox.jpeg"
			alt="Lockbox location"
			loading="lazy"
		/>

		<video
			class="instructionMedia"
			src="/photos/KeyTurn.mp4"
			controls
			playsinline
			muted
			preload="metadata"
		>
			Sorry, your browser doesn’t support embedded videos.
		</video>
	</div>

</div>
</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section" id="electricity">
		<div class="stepCard">
			<div class="stepText">
				<h2>Electricity (power)</h2>
				<p>
					The electricity will most likely be off on arrival. The fuse box is located <strong>just inside the front
					door</strong>, on the wall as you enter the kitchen. Flick the switch <strong>up</strong> to turn the
					power on.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="stepMedia">
				<img
	class="instructionPhoto"
	src="/photos/Power.jpeg"
	alt="Fuse box and power switch"
	loading="lazy"
/>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section" id="mains">
	<div class="stepCard">
		<div class="stepText">
			<h2>Water &amp; gas (mains)</h2>
			<p>
				On arrival, the <strong>water and gas mains may be switched off</strong>. The key to open the mains
				access is on a key hanger just inside the front door.
			</p>

			<ol>
				<li>Open the Gas and Water mains access at the front of the house using the key.</li>
				<li>
					Ensure both the <strong>gas</strong> and <strong>water</strong> are switched to the <strong>ON</strong> position.
				</li>
				<li>Once on, check the water flow, check hot water, and confirm the hob is working.</li>
			</ol>

			<div id="hob"></div>
		</div>

		<div class="stepMedia">
			<img
				class="instructionPhoto mainsLocationPhoto"
				src="/photos/MainsLocation.jpeg"
				alt="Gas and water mains access location"
				loading="lazy"
			/>
		</div>

		<div class="stepFullWidth">
			<p class="mainsLabel">Gas &amp; water switch positions:</p>

			<div class="mainsGridWrap">
				<div class="mainsGrid">
					<div class="mainsCorner"></div>
					<div class="mainsColHead">OFF</div>
					<div class="mainsColHead">ON</div>

					<div class="mainsRowHead">Gas</div>
					<img class="mainsImg" src="/photos/GasOff.jpeg" alt="Gas mains OFF" loading="lazy" />
					<img class="mainsImg" src="/photos/GasOn.jpeg" alt="Gas mains ON" loading="lazy" />

					<div class="mainsRowHead">Water</div>
					<img class="mainsImg" src="/photos/WaterOff.jpeg" alt="Water mains OFF" loading="lazy" />
					<img class="mainsImg" src="/photos/WaterOn.jpeg" alt="Water mains ON" loading="lazy" />
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="boilerRow" id="hot-water">
	<div>
		<h3>Hot water (boiler)</h3>
		<p>
			The button for the boiler is on the wall <strong>between the boiler and the window. Once switched on you should have hot water whenever you use the hot tap. </strong>. Once the mains
			are on, check that hot water is working.
		</p>
	</div>

	<img
		class="boilerPhoto"
		src="/photos/Boiler.jpeg"
		alt="Boiler / hot water button (between sink and fridge)"
		loading="lazy"
	/>
</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Windows &amp; shutters (mosquito nets)</h2>
		<p>
			Windows and shutters open from the inside. There is netting on the window frames to help keep out mosquitos.
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Lift/peel the net slightly from one corner to access the shutter latch.</li>
			<li>Open the shutter, then re-cover the frame with the netting.</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			If you’re not visiting in July/August, windows and fans may be all that’s needed to cool the house down in the evenings.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Air conditioning &amp; fans</h2>
		<p>
			There are portable air-con units in all rooms. Ensure the hose/cylinder at the back of the unit is connected to the wall vent so hot air is directed outside.
		</p>
		<p>
			<strong>Tip:</strong> If all units are on at the same time (upstairs and downstairs), it can blow the fuse. We recommend not running all units simultaneously.
			There are multiple fans you can use to supplement.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>If something doesn’t work…</h2>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Power keeps tripping:</strong> don’t run all portable air-con units at the same time (try one floor at a time).</li>
			<li><strong>No hot water:</strong> confirm water mains are ON, then check the boiler button (between sink and fridge).</li>
			<li><strong>Gas hob not working:</strong> confirm the gas mains are fully ON.</li>
			<li><strong>Front door key won’t come out:</strong> turn the key half a turn back, then remove.</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Internet (Wi‑Fi)</h2>
		<p>
			There is <strong>no Wi‑Fi</strong> in the house and mobile reception varies by provider. If you struggle for internet, consider an Italian eSIM
			(e.g. via Revolut or directly with a provider) after arriving.
		</p>
	</section>

	<style>
		.hero { margin-bottom: 10px; }
		.subhead { color: var(--muted); font-weight: 600; margin-top: -6px; }

		.section { margin-top: 22px; }
		h2 { margin-bottom: 8px; }
		h3 { margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 6px; }

		.callout {
			background: var(--card);
			border: 1px solid var(--border);
			border-radius: var(--radius);
			padding: 14px;
		}

		/* Checklist */
		.checklistCard {
			background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 8%, var(--card));
			border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 20%, var(--border));
			border-radius: var(--radius);
			padding: 14px 16px;
			margin-top: 12px;
		}
		.checklistCard h2 { margin: 0 0 8px; }
		.checklist { padding-left: 20px; margin: 0; }
		.checklist li { margin: 8px 0; }
		.checklist a { text-decoration: none; }
		.checklist a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

		/* Step cards */
		.stepCard {
			background: var(--card);
			border: 1px solid var(--border);
			border-radius: var(--radius);
			padding: 16px;
			display: grid;
			gap: 14px;
			align-items: start;
			margin-top: 14px;
		}
		@media (min-width: 860px) {
			.stepCard {
				grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 0.8fr;
				align-items: center;
			}
		}

        .stepFullWidth {
	grid-column: 1 / -1;
	margin-top: 8px;
}

		.stepCard h2 { margin: 0 0 6px; }
		.stepText p, .stepText ul, .stepText ol { margin: 8px 0; }

		.stepMedia {
	display: flex;
	align-items: flex-start;   /* keeps media aligned to the top */
	justify-content: flex-end; /* keeps media on the right */
	gap: 10px;
}

.stepMedia img,
.stepMedia video {
	margin-top: 0;
}

		/* Photos */
		.instructionPhoto {
			width: 100%;
			max-width: 360px;
			height: auto;
			display: block;
			border-radius: calc(var(--radius) - 2px);
			border: 1px solid var(--border);
			background: var(--bg);
		}

		/* Keep lists readable */
		ul, ol { padding-left: 20px; }
		li { margin: 6px 0; }

.mediaRow {
	display: grid;
	gap: 10px;
	justify-items: end;
}

/* Desktop: side-by-side */
@media (min-width: 860px) {
	.mediaRow {
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		align-items: start;
		justify-items: end;
	}
}

/* Video styling (match photo sizing) */
.instructionMedia {
	width: 100%;
	max-width: 360px;
	border-radius: calc(var(--radius) - 2px);
	border: 1px solid var(--border);
	background: #000;
	display: block;
}

.mediaCaption {
	margin: 8px 0 0;
	max-width: 720px; /* allows caption to sit under both items */
	color: var(--muted);
	font-size: 14px;
	font-weight: 600;
	text-align: right;
}

.mainsLocationPhoto {
	max-width: 320px;
}

.mainsLabel {
	margin: 0;
	color: var(--muted);
	font-weight: 700;
}

.mainsGridWrap {
	display: flex;
	justify-content: center;  /* centers the grid */
	margin-top: 8px;
}

.mainsGrid {
	display: grid;
	grid-template-columns: 70px 1fr 1fr;
	gap: 10px;
	align-items: start;
	width: 100%;
	max-width: 520px;         /* prevents it spreading too wide */
}

.mainsCorner { height: 1px; }

.mainsColHead {
	font-weight: 800;
	color: var(--accentHover);
	text-transform: uppercase;
	letter-spacing: 0.03em;
	font-size: 12px;
	padding-left: 4px;
}

.mainsRowHead {
	font-weight: 800;
	color: var(--accentHover);
	font-size: 13px;
	padding-top: 6px;
}

.mainsImg {
	width: 100%;
	height: 150px;
	object-fit: cover;
	border-radius: calc(var(--radius) - 2px);
	border: 1px solid var(--border);
	background: var(--bg);
	display: block;
}

.boilerPhoto {
	width: 100%;
	max-width: 280px;
	height: auto;
	display: block;
	margin-top: 10px;
	border-radius: calc(var(--radius) - 2px);
	border: 1px solid var(--border);
	background: var(--bg);
}

.boilerRow {
	margin-top: 12px;
	display: grid;
	gap: 12px;
	align-items: start;
}

.boilerRow h3 {
	margin: 0 0 6px;
}

.boilerRow p {
	margin: 0;
}

@media (min-width: 860px) {
	.boilerRow {
		grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 0.8fr;
		align-items: center;
	}
	.boilerRow .boilerPhoto {
		justify-self: end;
	}
}
	</style>
</Layout>